  <text>  HOW TO RESPOND TO A PAGE?

You can comment a Web page. Click the   button of the above tool bar. You will be first asked to input your name in the following dialog:

                                       

Choose a nickname (or whatever you feel comfortable with), and click OK. You will immediately see the following text box:

                                                    

Type your comment in the text box. When you are done, click the &quot;Submit&quot; button. Your comment will be stored in the server and viewable by the original page author and other visitors.

To view the comments attached to a page, click the   button, you will see the comment area appearing at the bottom of this page (meanwhile the button icon will change to  ), as is shown below:

           

To view what different persons interested in the current page said, just click on that person&apos;s name on the left. The corresponding comment will be shown on the right of the comment area.

To hide the comment area (in order to save space), click the   button.

When you download a page, you also get all the comments other people have made on the page before.

As it makes no sense, you cannot comment a page that is on your computer.</text>
